Demo program to download and serve yahoo finance data via a rest api.

Uses yfinance api to download historical data from yahoo finance.

Utilities:

1. yfetch: downloads data from yahoo finance using yfinance
           and saves individual tickers as parquet (compression=gzip)
           files split by year. 

2. yserv:  runs a rest service using fast-api package and provides
           the following end-points:
           a. tickers/: 
                       returns currently saved tickers
           b. returns/{ticker}/{start_date}/{end_date}: 
                       returns returns for ticker based on 
                       start/end dates
                       eg. returns/AAPL/20231004/20250926
           c. returns/{query_date}/{tickers}: 
                       returns returns for ticker/s based on 
                       query date
                       eg. returns/20250811/NVDA,MSFT,AAPL,GOOG,AMZN,META

Requirements: included in requirements.txt (pip freeze)

Data: includes parquet folder with 20+ rics and 2 years worth of data

usage:

 ./yfetch --help
Usage: yfetch.py [OPTIONS]

  yfinance downloader

Options:
  --tickers TEXT  ric or , seperated list of rics  [default: NVDA,MSFT,AAPL,GO
                  OG,AMZN,META,AVGO,TSLA,JPM,WMT,ORCL,LLY,V,MA,NFLX,XOM,JNJ,AB
                  BV,PLTR,COST,HD,BAC,PG]
  --period TEXT   1d,5d,1mo,3mo,6mo,1y,2y,5y,10y,ytd,max  [default: 5d]
  --help          Show this message and exit.


./yserv --help
Usage: yserv.py [OPTIONS]

  yfinance rest service

Options:
  --host TEXT     host  [default: 127.0.0.1]
  --port INTEGER  port  [default: 8000]
  --help          Show this message and exit.

